To determine if a number is prime in JavaScript, you can use the following method:

```javascript
function isPrime(num) {
    if (num <= 1) {
        return false;
    }
    for (let i = 2; i <= Math.sqrt(num); i++) {
        if (num % i === 0) {
            return false;
        }
    }
    return true;
}
```

This function checks if the given number is less than or equal to 1, in which case it's not prime. Then it iterates from 2 to the square root of the number to check if there are any divisors other than 1 and itself. If it finds any divisor, it returns false; otherwise, it returns true.

